      <div class="view-content">
        <div class="views-row views-row-1 views-row-odd views-row-first views-row-last">
      
  <div class="views-field views-field-php">        <span class="field-content"><a href="#" onclick="(function($) { $('#slideout').stop().animate({'right': '-400px'}, 500); }) (jQuery); return false;">[x]</a></span>  </div>  
  <div class="views-field views-field-title">        <span class="field-content"><a href="/2014/09/11/hayek-keynes-and-seeds-denial-thing-we-need-moment-fight-keynes">Hayek, Keynes and the Seeds of Denial: &quot;This is the Thing We Need at the Moment - to Fight Keynes!&quot;</a></span>  </div>  
  <div class="views-field views-field-field-bimage">        <div class="field-content"><img src="http://www.desmogblog.com/sites/beta.desmogblog.com/files/styles/slideout/public/blogimages/Friedrich_Hayek_portrait.jpg?itok=1Ij2pw-R" width="100" height="130" alt="" /></div>  </div>  
  <div class="views-field views-field-body">        <div class="field-content"><p dir="ltr"><em><span style="letter-spacing: 0.03em; line-height: 1.5em;">Hayek is the intellectual inspiration for neoliberal think tanks and their war against Socialism, government regulation and, today, climate science. But are these tankers really faithful to his ideas?</span></em></p>
<p><span style="letter-spacing: 0.03em; line-height: 1.5em;">As our story unfolds we will see that climate denial is the invention of a network of think tanks first established to promote free market ideology.</span></p>
